title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1974-10-19
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step, Me & My Uncle, Friend Of The Devil, Beat It On Down The Line, It Must Have Been The Roses, El Paso, Loose Lucy, Black Throated Wind, Scarlet Begonias, To Lay Me Down, Mama Tried, Eyes Of The World-> China Doll, Big River

Set 2

Phil & Ned*, Uncle John's Band, Big Railroad Blues, The Race is On, Tomorrow Is Forever, Mexicali Blues, Dire Wolf, Sugar Magnolia-> He's Gone-> Truckin'-> Caution (Do Not Stop on Tracks) Jam-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Black Peter, Sunshine Daydream, E: One More Saturday Night, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Great Sound! and more! easy to recommend!
Take a bite
Check out Donna as she an Jerry go to the place where she's moanin' and yellin', and Jerry is playing off her!
Very Pig-like... meaning, I know I've heard Jerry and Pig doing it on recordings when Pig was at his best!
   I'm sure there's other shows where he and Donna pull this off, as this doesn't sound like the first time, but it really caught my ear! Works!!
